  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Deseed your <strong>peppers</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and slice into very thin strips</p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>red onion[s]</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) over a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced peppers</strong> and <strong>onion</strong> with a generous splash of <strong>cold water</strong> and cook for 15 min or until starting to caramelise</p><p>Tip: Stir occasionally to stop it from burning</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Once the onion and pepper is starting to caramelise, reduce the heat to medium and add 2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tsp] </span><strong>sugar </strong>with your <strong>red wine vinegar</strong></p><p>Cook for a further 30 secs or until slightly jammy</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>plant based</strong> <strong>'Nduja </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) with your <strong>tomato paste</strong> and the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and give it a good mix up</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>red wine stock paste </strong>and<strong> vegetable stock mix </strong>with your<strong> orzo</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Add 500ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [750ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1L] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Add a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium-low and cook, covered, for 12-13 min or until cooked with a slight bite – this is your <strong>veggie 'nduja & peperonata orzo</strong></p><p>Tip: Stir the orzo occasionally to stop it from sticking</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the orzo is cooked, tear your <strong>goats' cheese </strong>over (don't mix!) with a generous grind of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Set aside, covered, for 1-2 min or until the cheese is slightly melted – this is your <strong>one pan veggie 'nduja & peperonata orzo with goats' cheese</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>one pan veggie 'nduja & peperonata orzo with goats' cheese</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    }
  ],
